{"_type":"issue","id":"pdoc-id1","title":"Publish PortableDoc as an open design-token spec — variant catalog as JSON schema with reference renders for CSS, OOXML styles.xml, EPUB CSS, and email; backend interface for custom render targets in ~100 LOC","description":"Publish PortableDoc as an open design-token spec — variant catalog as JSON/Zod schema with reference renders for CSS, OOXML styles.xml seed, EPUB CSS, and email inline styles; backend interface for custom render targets in ~100 LOC.\n\nBOUND DECISIONS (no grill — momentum mode, recommendations accepted):\n 1. Package name: @portable-doc/design-tokens (published from packages/design-tokens/)\n 2. Schema definition: Zod (consistent with the envelope schema from Goal B); JSON Schema is a derived export via zod-to-json-schema\n 3. Versioning: SemVer of the package; major bumps when variant axes (tone/emphasis/family) change shape\n 4. Reference renders shipped: CSS, OOXML styles.xml seed, EPUB CSS, email inline-styles\n 5. Backend interface: TypeScript interface PortableDocBackend with adapter pattern; example custom backend (PDF stub) in ~100 LOC\n 6. Spec home: ~/docs/paperflow/specs/ for now; public site URL is post-v1\n 7. Catalog source of truth: packages/variants stays canonical; @portable-doc/design-tokens is a publishable view of it (re-exports + the schema + renderers)\n 8. License: MIT (matches the rest of the monorepo)","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-05-19T19:38:24Z","created_by":"pelle","updated_at":"2026-05-19T19:48:40Z","closed_at":"2026-05-19T19:48:40Z","close_reason":"All children completed","labels":["goal-design-tokens-spec","umbrella-pioneer-moves"],"dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":0}
